            <title>[FLINK-18519] Propagate exception to client when execution fails for REST submission</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-18519</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently when a user submits an application using the REST api and the execution fails, the exception is logged, but not sent back to the client. This issue aims at propagating the reason back to the client so that it is easier for the user to debug his/her application.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
